Documentation forAiConomist - React Nextjs Personal Blog Template

Created by: Platol

Created Date: 28/07/2024

Last Update: 28/07/2024

Files Structure

  • template-files/app - Directory of All Pages
  • template-files/app/components - Directory of Components Files
  • template-files/config - Directory of Configaration files
  • template-files/content - Directory of All Contents
  • template-files/data - Directory of All Generated JSON data
  • template-files/libs - Directory of Library files
  • template-files/libs/utils - Directory of Utility files
  • template-files/public - Directory of Images
  • template-files/styles - Directory of Styles/SCSS files

Installation

Checkout Official Next.js Documentation if you need.

System Requirements

  • Node.js 16.8.0 or later
  • MacOS, Windows (including WSL), and Linux are supported

Install dependencies in your project:

Nevigate to `template-files/` then open terminal and install dependencies by running

    npm install
    # or
    yarn  # if you have Yarn installed

Run `npm run dev` or `yarn dev`

to start development server in your local machine

    npm run dev
    # or
    yarn dev  # if you have Yarn installed

Now Open http://localhost:3000 with your browser to see the result.

Navbar Menu Update

Open `template-files/config/main-menu.json`

Customize(Add or Remove) menu Links by Changing the `name` and `link` value


  [
    {
      "name": "Home",
      "submenu": [
        {
          "name": "Home 01",
          "link": "/"
        },
        ....
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "About",
      "link": "/about"
    },
    {
      "name": "All Posts",
      "link": "/blog"
    },
    {
      "name": "Pages",
      "submenu": [
        {
          "name": "Elements",
          "link": "/blog/elements"
        },
        {
          "name": "All Authors",
          "link": "/author"
        },
        ....

    },

ALL CONTENTS ARE IN MARKDOWN/MDX FORMAT

Markdown Cheat Sheet MDX Doc

Home Content Update

Open `template-files/content/_index.mdx`

Customize Home content by Changing the values (supports markdown)

Adding New Blog Post

Open `template-files/content/blog/` directory, you will find all blog posts here.

Add New or Customize existing Blog Post by following

You can use React Components in your blog post app/components/MDXcomponents.js
Check the existing components in app/components/MDXcomponents.js or add your own

How to use Image in Blog Post

  
    <CustomImage
      src="/images/blog/post-11.jpg" 
      alt="image" 
      height="485" 
      width="1000"
      caption="This is a Image Caption"
    />

How to use Video in Blog Post

  
    # Youtube video
    <CustomVideo title="" type="youtube" video_id="CHSnz0bCaUk" />
  
  
    # Vimeo video
    <CustomVideo title="" type="vimeo" video_id="341490793" />

Adding a New Author or Video Post is same as Adding a New Blog Post

Open `template-files/content/author/` or `template-files/content/vidoes/` directory,
you will find all files there.

Check the existing files copy and paste One then edit the content as your need

Contact Page content Update

Update the Contact Page content by editing

`template-files/content/pages/contact.mdx` file content.

Contact form works with https://formsubmit.co/

Update `contactForm` informations

  • `email: "youremailhere@gmail.com"`
    update email with your email-address to recive the message directly to your email.
  • `mailSubject: "Message form AiConomist Next.js!"`
    when somebody will send message from website then it will show on the Email Subject.
  • Also successMassage and errorMessage

SCSS Files & Structure

SCSS and Next.js Module Files
Change TailwindCSS config (if you need) from
`template-files/tailwind.config.js`

Changing Font

This template uses 'Lexend Deca' and 'Prata' Font from the Google Fonts Library
To change the Font, Open `app/components/essential/Fonts.js`

Follow the Official Guide of @next/font

or Watch this tutorial by `Lee Robinson` - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L8_98i_bMMA


and use the font like below
